### Phase 2 -- Real-time update

#### 2.1 Parse `custom-title` in ClaudeLineParser (src/agents/claude/claude-agent.ts)

In the `format()` method's switch statement (line 567-583), add a case:

```typescript
case 'custom-title': {
  const customTitle = (data as { customTitle?: string }).customTitle;
  if (customTitle) {
    return `Session renamed: "${customTitle}"`;
  }
  return '';
}
```

This makes the parser emit a `ParsedLine` with `type: 'custom-title'` and a formatted message. The PrettyFormatter will display it with a generic type label (the `default` case in `formatType` gives `CUST`).

#### 2.2 Add `isCustomTitle` and `customTitleValue` to ParsedLine (src/core/types.ts)

Extend `ParsedLine` with two optional fields:

```typescript
export interface ParsedLine {
  // ... existing fields ...
  /** custom-title event detected (Claude only) */
  isCustomTitle?: boolean;
  /** The new custom title value */
  customTitleValue?: string;
}
```

Update `ClaudeLineParser.format()` to return these fields when parsing `custom-title`:

```typescript
case 'custom-title': {
  const customTitle = (data as { customTitle?: string }).customTitle;
  if (!customTitle) return '';
  // Return formatted string (the parse() caller will build the ParsedLine)
  return `Session renamed: "${customTitle}"`;
}
```

But wait -- `format()` only returns a string. The `parse()` method at line 417 builds the `ParsedLine`. We need to set `isCustomTitle` and `customTitleValue` there. The cleanest approach: handle `custom-title` as a special case in `parse()`, similar to how `assistant` and `toolUseResult` are handled:

```typescript
// In parse(), before the generic format() call:
if (type === 'custom-title') {
  const customTitle = data.customTitle as string;
  if (!customTitle) return null;
  return {
    type: 'custom-title',
    timestamp,
    raw: data,
    formatted: `Session renamed: "${customTitle}"`,
    isCustomTitle: true,
    customTitleValue: customTitle,
  };
}
```

This is cleaner than trying to smuggle the data through `format()`.

#### 2.3 Add `updateSessionDisplayName` to SessionManager (src/core/session-manager.ts)

```typescript
/**
 * Update a session's displayName (e.g., when custom-title changes)
 */
updateSessionDisplayName(id: string, displayName: string): void {
  const session = this.sessions.find((s) => s.id === id);
  if (session) {
    session.displayName = displayName;
  }
}
```

#### 2.4 Add `onTitleUpdate` callback to `OnLineHandlerConfig` (src/claude/watch-builder.ts)

Extend the config interface:

```typescript
export interface OnLineHandlerConfig {
  // ... existing fields ...
  /** Callback when a custom-title event is detected on MAIN session */
  onTitleUpdate?: (title: string) => void;
}
```

In `createOnLineHandler`, after the line `config.onOutput(config.formatter.format(parsed), label);`, add:

```typescript
// Real-time custom-title update
if (label === MAIN_LABEL && parsed.isCustomTitle && parsed.customTitleValue) {
  config.onTitleUpdate?.(parsed.customTitleValue);
}
```

#### 2.5 Wire up real-time title update in `startClaudeMultiWatch` (src/index.ts)

When creating the `onLine` handler, pass `onTitleUpdate`:

```typescript
createOnLineHandler({
  parsers,
  formatter,
  detector,
  onOutput: (formatted) => console.log(formatted),
  verbose: options.verbose,
  shouldOutput,
  onTitleUpdate: (title) => {
    // In non-interactive mode, just log
