1. **Unit test: `readCustomTitle`** (new file: `tests/claude/custom-title.test.ts`)
   - File with no custom-title entries returns null
   - File with one custom-title returns the title
   - File with multiple custom-title entries returns the last one
   - Empty file returns null
   - File with invalid JSON lines (gracefully ignored)
   - custom-title with empty string returns null

2. **Unit test: ClaudeLineParser custom-title** (extend `tests/agents/claude-agent.test.ts`)
   - `parse()` of a `custom-title` line returns `ParsedLine` with `type: 'custom-title'`, `isCustomTitle: true`, `customTitleValue` set
   - Empty customTitle returns null
   - Verify no infinite loop (use existing `collectAllParsedLines` pattern)

3. **Unit test: SessionManager.updateSessionDisplayName** (extend `tests/core/session-manager.test.ts`)
   - Updating displayName on existing session works
